Subject: [PATCH] Options: skip the wasm coherence check when WebAssembly is off

riscv64 C_LOOP builds compile WebAssembly out (WebKit forbids
ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY together with ENABLE_C_LOOP, see webkit-patches/0004),
but Options::useWasm() still defaults to true. assertOptionsAreCoherent()
then reports

    INCOHERENT OPTIONS: at least one of useWasmIPInt, or useBBQJIT must be true

at VM initialization, because both wasm interpreters are compiled out.
That aborts before executing ANY JavaScript (only `bun --version`, which
never spins up the VM, works). The check is meaningless when WebAssembly
is not built, so compile it out under #if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY). The agent
shipped on this runtime uses Postgres rather than the WebAssembly PGlite
build, so no wasm execution is required.

diff --git a/Source/JavaScriptCore/runtime/Options.cpp b/Source/JavaScriptCore/runtime/Options.cpp
index d9ebf57..de661a4 100644
--- a/Source/JavaScriptCore/runtime/Options.cpp
+++ b/Source/JavaScriptCore/runtime/Options.cpp
@@ -1392,10 +1392,12 @@ void Options::assertOptionsAreCoherent()
         coherent = false;
         dataLog("INCOHERENT OPTIONS: at least one of useLLInt or useJIT must be true\n");
     }
+#if ENABLE(WEBASSEMBLY)
     if (useWasm() && !(useWasmIPInt() || useBBQJIT())) {
         coherent = false;
         dataLog("INCOHERENT OPTIONS: at least one of useWasmIPInt, or useBBQJIT must be true\n");
     }
+#endif
     if (useProfiler() && useConcurrentJIT()) {
         coherent = false;
         dataLogLn("Bytecode profiler is not concurrent JIT safe.");
